# Command-Line Networking Tools

## Lab Overview
Explores the various CLI commands that can be used to gain information about the network a device is part of and some basic ways to troubleshoot the network

## Objectives

- Understand the information that is presented from various commands
- Identify network details that can be used as baselines
- Learn how to use arguments to present more information about a network

## Key Concepts

| ipconfig | provides configuration information about the network to which the device is currently connectected |
| ping | used with either a hostname or IP address. Sends an ICMP packet to target to verify if it can be reached |
| tracert| traces the network route that the ICMP packet traverses to reach a target system, showing each 'jump' taken on the way to the target |
| nslookup | finds the IP address associated with a given host/domain name
| netstat | displays the current network connections and listening ports. Can be altered to present more information by use of arguments such as -b, -o, -n |

